article.description: Stefan Jankovic had 14 points and 12 rebounds to lead Hawaii past Arkansas-Pine Bluff 75-47 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Hawaii tops Arkansas-Pine Bluff 75-47
article.story: HONOLULU -- Stefan Jankovic had 14 points and 12 rebounds to lead Hawaii past Arkansas-Pine Bluff 75-47 on Wednesday night. Jankovic finished 5 of 9 from the field for Hawaii (5-1). Isaac Flemming had 13 points and Sai Tummal added 12. Ghiavonni Robinson scored 14 points for Arkansas-Pine Bluff (2-6). JoVaughn Love added 11 points and six rebounds. Hawaii went on a 24-11 run to take a 36-25 lead at the half. The Rainbow Warriors had a huge advantage at the free-throw line, making 22 of 33 to the Golden Lions' 2 of 4. Hawaii only made 1 of 11 from 3-point range, while Arkansas-Pine Bluff went 5 of 28. --- This story has been corrected to show dateline Honolulu.
